---

Private npm registry — Conventions for Turborepo + bun + Docker:

Architecture:
- Single `.npmrc` at monorepo root — NEVER `.npmrc` in `apps/` or `packages/`
- Bun automatically reads the root `.npmrc` for all workspaces
- Token via env interpolation `${NPM_TOKEN}` — NEVER hardcoded tokens
- Each private scope = one `@scope:registry=URL` line + one `//URL/:_authToken=${TOKEN}` line

Token flow in Docker:
- `.env` → `compose.yaml` (`build.args`) → `Dockerfile` (`ARG` + `ENV`) → `.npmrc` → `bun install`
- Token is passed via `build.args` (build-time), NOT via `environment` (runtime)
- Only services with private dependencies receive the token

Dockerfile security (MANDATORY):
- `ARG NPM_TOKEN` + `ENV NPM_TOKEN=${NPM_TOKEN}` at the beginning of the deps stage
- `COPY .npmrc .npmrc` BEFORE `bun install`
- `RUN rm -f .npmrc` + `ENV NPM_TOKEN=` AFTER `bun install`
- The runtime stage (stage 2) must contain neither `.npmrc` nor `NPM_TOKEN`
- Only `node_modules` is copied from the deps stage to the runtime stage

compose.yaml:
- `build.args.NPM_TOKEN: ${NPM_TOKEN:-}` — empty default value
- `context: .` must point to the monorepo root (access to `.npmrc`)

.env.example:
- Document each token variable: `NPM_TOKEN=`
- Dedicated section `# ─── NPM Private Registry ───`

.dockerignore:
- `.npmrc` must NOT be in `.dockerignore` (needed for the build)
- `.env` MUST be in `.dockerignore` (contains the actual token)

Related skill: `.cursor/skills/npm-private-registry/SKILL.md` — full procedure, checklist, debugging

Avoid:
- Hardcoded token in `.npmrc`, Dockerfile, or compose.yaml
- `.npmrc` in sub-packages
- `NPM_TOKEN` in `environment` (unnecessary at runtime, leak risk)
- `.npmrc` in `.dockerignore`
- `bun install` on the host to resolve private packages
